<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id62db5671-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa" identifier="/us/usc/t25/s5131"><num value="5131">§ 5131.</num><heading> Publication of list of recognized tribes</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id62db5672-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa" identifier="/us/usc/t25/s5131/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> Publication of list</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary shall publish in the Federal Register a list of all Indian tribes which the Secretary recognizes to be eligible for the special programs and services provided by the United States to Indians because of their status as Indians.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id62db5673-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa" identifier="/us/usc/t25/s5131/b"><num value="b" class="bold">(b)</num><heading class="bold"> Frequency of publication</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The list shall be published within 60 days of <date date="1994-11-02">November 2, 1994</date>, and annually on or before every January 30 thereafter.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="id62db5674-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa">(<ref href="/us/pl/103/454/tI/s104">Pub. L. 103–454, title I, § 104</ref>, <date date="1994-11-02">Nov. 2, 1994</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/108/4792">108 Stat. 4792</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
